winning_structure.name: UBX-MON-RF
winning_structure.description: Information for each RF block. There are as many RF blocks reported as bands supported by this receiver.

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x00 for this version)

fields.name: nBlocks
fields.description: The number of RF blocks included

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: blockId
fields.description: RF block ID (0 = L1 band, 1 = L2 or L5 band depending on product configuration)

fields.name: flags
fields.description: Output from jamming/interference monitor (0 = unknown or feature disabled or flag unavailable, 1 = ok - no significant jamming, 2 = warning - interference visible but fix OK, 3 = critical - interference visible and no fix). This flag is deprecated in protocol versions that support UBX-SEC-SIG (version 0x02) and always reported as 0; instead jammingState in UBX-SEC-SIG should be monitored.

bits.name: jammingState
bits.description: Output from jamming/interference monitor (0 = unknown or feature disabled or flag unavailable, 1 = ok - no significant jamming, 2 = warning - interference visible but fix OK, 3 = critical - interference visible and no fix). This flag is deprecated in protocol versions that support UBX-SEC-SIG (version 0x02) and always reported as 0; instead jammingState in UBX-SEC-SIG should be monitored.

fields.name: antStatus
fields.description: Status of the antenna supervisor state machine (0x00=INIT, 0x01=DONTKNOW, 0x02=OK, 0x03=SHORT, 0x04=OPEN)

fields.name: antPower
fields.description: Current power status of antenna (0x00=OFF, 0x01=ON, 0x02=DONTKNOW)

fields.name: postStatus
fields.description: POST status word

fields.name: reserved1
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: noisePerMS
fields.description: Noise level as measured by the GPS core

fields.name: agcCnt
fields.description: AGC Monitor, as percentage of maximum gain, range 0 to 8191 (100%)

fields.name: cwSuppression
fields.description: CW interference suppression level, scaled (0=no CW jamming, 255 = strong CW jamming)

fields.name: ofsI
fields.description: Imbalance of I-part of complex signal, scaled (-128 = max. negative imbalance, 127 = max. positive imbalance)

fields.name: magI
fields.description: Magnitude of I-part of complex signal, scaled (0 = no signal, 255 = max.magnitude)

fields.name: ofsQ
fields.description: Imbalance of Q-part of complex signal, scaled (-128 = max. negative imbalance, 127 = max. positive imbalance)

fields.name: magQ
fields.description: Magnitude of Q-part of complex signal, scaled (0 = no signal, 255 = max.magnitude)

fields.name: reserved2
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: version
fields.description: Message version (0x00 for this version)

fields.name: nBlocks
fields.description: The number of RF blocks included

fields.name: reserved0
fields.description: Reserved

fields.name: blockId
fields.description:
RF block ID, this is a unique value assigned to every RF block.
The band which the RF block represents is subject to product configuration.

bits.name: jammingState
bits.description: Output from jamming/interference monitor (0 = unknown or feature disabled or flag unavailable, 1 = ok - no significant jamming, 2 = warning - interference visible but fix OK, 3 = critical - interference visible and no fix). This flag is deprecated in protocol versions that support UBX-SEC-SIG (version 0x02) and always reported as 0; instead jammingState in UBX-SEC-SIG should be monitored.
